<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
    Entitlements for max_clawdroom. Paired with codesign's runtime
    option to enable the Hardened Runtime (required for notarization).

    NOT sandboxed. The app reads other processes' UI via the
    Accessibility API (EditorAwareness → kAXDocumentAttribute,
    kAXSelectedTextRangeAttribute) which is explicitly incompatible
    with the App Sandbox. Developer ID distribution permits this;
    Mac App Store distribution would not.

    HISTORICAL NOTE: earlier versions enabled `allow-jit`,
    `allow-unsigned-executable-memory`, `disable-library-validation`,
    and `allow-dyld-environment-variables` to support the MLX/Kokoro-82M
    voice path. MLX was removed in 0.1.1; those entitlements have been
    dropped. If you re-introduce a JIT'd shader / library-loaded
    backend, re-add ONLY what that backend needs and document why.
    -->

    <!-- Network: claude-code CLI talks to Anthropic's API. We don't
         open sockets ourselves today, but future agent actions
         might (e.g. fetching documentation, URL previews). -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Mic + speech recognition for the wake-on-voice slice and the
         hold-to-talk hotkey. Paired with Info.plist usage descriptions. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
    NOT requested:
    - com.apple.security.app-sandbox (incompatible with AX reads)
    - com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit (no JIT path now MLX is gone)
    - com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory (ditto)
    - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation (no unsigned dylibs ship)
    - com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables (we strip
      DYLD_* explicitly before launching the claude subprocess; see
      ClaudeCodeProcess.start())
    - com.apple.security.automation.apple-events (AX is its own TCC
      bucket, granted separately by the user)
    - com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write (state files
      live under ~/Library/Application Support/Companion/ which a
      non-sandboxed app can write to without a prompt)
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
